# Intentionally parallel code — structurally identical by design.
# A pair is suppressed only when BOTH functions match the SAME pattern.
# Pattern syntax: filepath.Match globs against function names (e.g., "(Type).Method*").
# Pair syntax: "FuncA <-> FuncB" — suppresses a specific cross-function pair.

# === Same-pattern suppressions (both sides match one glob) ===

# Event logger methods — each Log* method wraps l.Log() with event-specific data.
# They are parallel by design; flagging them as clones buries real findings.
(Logger).Log*

# Event logger adapter methods — same pattern as Logger.
(EventLoggerAdapter).Log*

# Daemon periodic handlers — each handle*Result processes a different check
# result type with identical error-handling structure.
handle*Result

# Beads line parsers — parseBeadsIDs and parseBeadsLine parse different formats
# with similar AST shape. Same for ParseBeadsLine (exported variant).
parseBeads*
ParseBeads*

# Threshold derivation — DeriveInvariantThreshold and DeriveVerificationThreshold
# look up different threshold types with identical lookup structure.
Derive*Threshold

# Workspace field readers — ReadReviewTierFromWorkspace and ReadVerifyLevelFromWorkspace
# read different YAML fields with identical file-read boilerplate.
Read*FromWorkspace

# Issue category finders — findPhantomIssues and findZombieIssues detect different
# categories using the same iteration pattern.
find*Issues

# Beads issue inference — inferBrowserToolFromBeadsIssue and inferMCPFromBeadsIssue
# infer different config from issue labels with identical branching structure.
infer*FromBeadsIssue

# SpawnTime getter variants — SpawnTime (method) and readSpawnTime (helper)
# are a getter/reader pair with near-identical bodies.
*SpawnTime

# Self-match suppressions — identical function matched against itself due to
# appearing in both modified and corpus partitions. (Detector bug, but suppress
# until the dedup fix lands.)
inferSkillFromBeadsIssue
InferSkillFromIssueType

# === Pair-pattern suppressions (cross-function FPs) ===

# JSONL writers — Logger.Log writes events, WriteCheckpoint writes daemon state.
# Both serialize to JSONL with identical marshal-and-append structure but
# completely different domains.
(Logger).Log* <-> WriteCheckpoint

# Git diff parsers — getWebChangesFromRecentCommits looks for web/ paths,
# hasGoChangesInRecentCommits looks for .go paths. Same git-log parsing,
# different filters.
getWebChangesFromRecentCommits <-> hasGoChangesInRecentCommits

# Context generators — GenerateEcosystemContext builds spawn context,
# loadOrchSkillContent and collectReflectSuggestions load skill/reflect data.
# Similar file-read-and-concatenate shape, different purposes.
GenerateEcosystemContext <-> loadOrchSkillContent
GenerateEcosystemContext <-> collectReflectSuggestions

# Opposite beads operations — CloseIssue and GetComments share CLI invocation
# boilerplate but perform complementary operations.
CloseIssue <-> GetComments

# String extraction helpers — getBeadsIssuePrefix extracts issue ID prefix,
# getGitBaseline reads git baseline. Both parse strings with similar structure.
getBeadsIssuePrefix <-> getGitBaseline
